sentences: Donna Jean Hilley (born Whitten, June 30, 1940 – June 20, 2012) was an American music publishing executive who served as CEO of Sony/ATV Music Publishing from 1994 to her retirement in 2005.
Originally from Birmingham, Alabama, Hilley began her career at WKDA in Nashville and went on to work in country music publishing.
Her mother, Janie Mae Whitten (née Sizemore) was a stay at home mom when Donna was born at home after a long difficult labor (many births occurred at home in the rural South in those days).
Her brother, Jimmy Whitten, was born 5 years later, and a sister Diane Whitten, was born 14 years later.
Several years later Hilley followed one of the disc jockeys from WKDA into his advertising firm, Bill Hudson and Associates.
In 1980 Donna and Rayford were surprised with the birth of their third daughter Whitney (19 & 21 years younger than Vickie and Debbie).
Several years later her previous boss at the radio station had also been running a music publishing company, Tree.
